Package org.jaudiotagger.tag.virtual

Class Summary
VirtualMetaDataContainer A VirtualMetaDataContainer can hold data from any tag type and can be used to convert between tags The tag format cannot currently be persisted to file it is intended for use in memory to allow the processing of tags by other applications through a common interface without having to know the internal workings of different audio types.
VirtualMetaDataItem Header for a MetaDataItem
VirtualMetaDataItemFactory Constructs a VirtualMetaDataItem from a ID3v24 Frame
VirtualMetaItemID3v24Conversion Handles the mapping from ID3v24 to VirtualmetaDataItem(s) In most cases there is straight forward one to one mapping but in some cases the ID3v24tag can map to a number of different VirtualDatametaItems depending upon the data in the ID3v24 tag.
